  "issue_number": 1099,
  "issue_title": "[Bug] Repository registration rejects common GitHub repository URLs",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\nThe repository registration form only accepts an exact root repository URL such as `https://github.com/owner/repo`. Common GitHub URLs copied from a browser can include query strings, hash fragments, or repository subpaths, such as `?tab=readme-ov-file`, `#readme`, or `/tree/main`.\n\nThe parser/validator should normalize these URLs to `owner/repo` before validation and mirror tracking checks.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Open `/repository-registration`.\n2. Enter a repository URL copied from GitHub with a suffix, for example `https://github.com/owner/repo?tab=readme-ov-file`.\n3. Fill the rest of the form and confirm the GitHub App installation.\n4. Submit the form.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nThe form should normalize valid GitHub repository URLs to `owner/repo` before validation and mirror tracking checks. These should resolve to the same repository:\n\n- `https://github.com/owner/repo`\n- `https://github.com/owner/repo?tab=readme-ov-file`\n- `https://github.com/owner/repo#readme`\n- `https://github.com/owner/repo/tree/main`\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nThe form either rejects the URL or checks a malformed repo name such as `owner/repo?tab=readme-ov-file` against the mirror health response. That can incorrectly show the repository as not installed/tracked.\n\n## Environment\n\n- Browser: Any\n- OS: Any\n\n## Additional Context\n\nThis is a follow-up edge case in the repository registration flow. A narrow fix can parse with `URL`, extract only the first two path segments, and reject URLs that do not contain a valid owner/repo pair.",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-16T19:07:11.000Z",
